cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.SI 

The paper deals with using machine learning techniques to detect the surgical workflow phase from intra-operative signals. This involves processing and interpreting sensor data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques in the context of a modern operating room, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the use of machine-readable forms of data, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
